result.execSummary:
The defendant Chester L. Boho Jr. was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Chester L. Boho Jr. is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Chester L. Boho Jr. was found guilty of Possession of Methamphetamine [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

records.addlTxt:
2:15 pm - DA calls cases 16CF62 and 16CM91 and states appearances and agreement reached. Defendant Chester L. Boho appeared with attorney Bryce Alan Schoenborn.  Mark T. Fuhr appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty Schoenborn gives court a waiver of preliminary hearing form on 16CF62.  Court questions DE regarding form.  Court accepts waiver.  Information filed, acknowledged and reading waived.  Court orders Ct 1 on 16CF62 amended to possess amphetamine, contrary to 961.41(3g)(g), a class I felony.  DE enters plea of NO CONTEST to count 1 in each case.  Court questions DE regarding the plea and plea questionnaire.  DA explains elements of charge.  Court finds plea/waiver to be free, etc.  Court finds factual basis does exist.  Court accepts plea, finds DE guilty and orders entry of JOC on Ct 1 in each case and on motion of DA, dismisses Ct 2 in each case.  DE to submit DNA sample at PRSO.  Court imposes:

16CF62, Ct 1 - Sentence withheld, 3 years probation
Conditions of probation
$350 fine
$250 DNAAS
Submit to AODA assessment within 30 days and comply with any recommendations.
80 days in jail with huber, consecutive to any other

16CM91, Ct 1 - Sentence withheld, 1 year probation
Conditions of probation
$243 court costs
$200 DNAAS
Submit to AODA assessment within 30 days and comply with any recommendations.
10 days in jail with huber, consecutive to any other

DE told that he may not vote or possess firearms

Appeal rights given
